race.comment: HONEY MAKER (6) broke through for a narrow maiden win last time out at Pakenham and can keep the ball rolling. She'd been threatening to win one and this looks a very sensible option, barely harder than that maiden she won last start. EVERETT (5) is finding it tough to crack another win, okay last time in this grade at Ararat having placed in three runs prior. She's consistent however and should run another strong race. HERE COMES RUBY (1) resumes. She was last seen winning a decent maiden over 2000m at Mornington and may have improved now into her second preparation. This looks a good trip for her to resume at. CUMBRIAN QUEEN (7) is racing well and draws for every chance up on speed. She should be right there. SNAPPY PIERRO (4) was too good for a 0-56 field last time and has claims off that.
